    {
      "number": 2,
      "id": "I_kwDOJTh_ks5i6Ort",
      "title": "tags reco from 8819",
      "url": "https://github.com/boucadair/rfc8407bis/issues/2",
      "state": "CLOSED",
      "author": "boucadair",
      "authorAssociation": "OWNER",
      "assignees": [
        "boucadair"
      ],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "> [6.1. ](https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc8819#section-6.1)[Define Standard Tags](https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc8819#name-define-standard-tags)\r\n> A module MAY indicate, using module-tag extension statements, a set of tags that are to be automatically associated with it (i.e., not added through configuration).\r\n> \r\n> module example-module {\r\n>   namespace \"https://example.com/yang/example\";\r\n>   prefix \"ex\";\r\n>   //...\r\n>   import module-tags { prefix tags; }\r\n> \r\n>   tags:module-tag \"ietf:some-new-tag\";\r\n>   tags:module-tag \"ietf:some-other-tag\";\r\n>   // ...\r\n> }\r\n> The module writer can use existing standard tags or use new tags defined in the model definition, as appropriate. For IETF standardized modules, new tags MUST be assigned in the IANA registry defined below, see [Section 7.2](https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc8819#sec-ietf-yang-module-tags-registry).",
      "createdAt": "2023-04-08T07:33:15Z",
      "updatedAt": "2023-10-18T10:20:02Z",
      "closedAt": "2023-10-18T10:20:02Z",
      "comments": []
    },
    {
      "number": 4,
      "id": "I_kwDOJTh_ks5v4hhX",
      "title": "List name: singular or plural",
      "url": "https://github.com/boucadair/rfc8407bis/issues/4",
      "state": "CLOSED",
      "author": "boucadair",
      "authorAssociation": "OWNER",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "The convention is to have the list name singular, and surrounding container name plural. I would think someone just accidentally reversed the convention.",
      "createdAt": "2023-09-01T09:35:03Z",
      "updatedAt": "2023-10-18T10:20:28Z",
      "closedAt": "2023-10-18T10:20:28Z",
      "comments": []
    },
    {
      "number": 5,
      "id": "I_kwDOJTh_ks5w62fn",
      "title": "Module Update (rfc7950#section-11)",
      "url": "https://github.com/boucadair/rfc8407bis/issues/5",
      "state": "OPEN",
      "author": "boucadair",
      "authorAssociation": "OWNER",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "From Ladislav Lhotka (ladislav.lhotka@nic.cz)\r\n\r\n> \"I have actually always thought that the section \"Updating a Module\" should never have become part of the YANG language definition. A sensible approach could IMO be to move this section to 8407bis, and relax the requirements to SHOULD there.\"\r\n\r\nFrom Rob:\r\n\r\nrfc7950#section-11\r\n>    Otherwise, if the semantics of any previous definition are changed\r\n>    (i.e., if a non-editorial change is made to any definition other than\r\n>    those specifically allowed above), then this MUST be achieved by a\r\n>    new definition with a new identifier.\r\n> \r\n> to\r\n> \r\n>    Otherwise, if the semantics of any previous definition are changed\r\n>    (i.e., if a non-editorial change is made to any definition other than\r\n>    those specifically allowed above), then this SHOULD be achieved by a\r\n>    new definition with a new identifier.\r\n",
      "createdAt": "2023-09-13T12:57:37Z",
      "updatedAt": "2023-09-13T12:57:37Z",
      "closedAt": null,
      "comments": []
    },
