    {
      "number": 7,
      "id": "I_kwDOJTh_ks5yXBux",
      "title": "SHOULD use mutual authentication when any sensitive data is being retrieved or modified",
      "url": "https://github.com/boucadair/rfc8407bis/issues/7",
      "state": "CLOSED",
      "author": "boucadair",
      "authorAssociation": "OWNER",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "From Rich Salz:\r\n\r\n> I read the security considerations carefully. It did a nice job\r\n> pointing out that some of the data could be sensitive so be careful\r\n> about exposing it to everyone. The opening sentence \"Both of these\r\n> protocols have mandatory-to-implement secure transport layers (e.g.,\r\n> SSH, TLS) with mutual authentication.\"\r\n Should probably be followed\r\n> with some kind of advice about SHOULD use mutual authentication when\r\n> any sensitive data is being retrieved or modified.\r\n> \r\n",
      "createdAt": "2023-09-29T05:55:10Z",
      "updatedAt": "2023-10-17T15:07:27Z",
      "closedAt": "2023-10-17T15:07:26Z",
      "comments": []
    },
