    {
      "number": 17,
      "id": "I_kwDOJTh_ks50dlqN",
      "title": "From Michal:  Inconsistency in section 4.6.2",
      "url": "https://github.com/boucadair/rfc8407bis/issues/17",
      "state": "CLOSED",
      "author": "boucadair",
      "authorAssociation": "OWNER",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "mvasko@cesnet.cz:\r\n\r\n> But, I found an inconsistency in section 4.6.2. where the example at\r\n> the\r\n> end mentions identities but uses them without their prefix. Then,\r\n> section 4.6.4. mentions that the prefix should always be used and uses\r\n> it in its example but fails to use `derived-from-or-self()` mentioned\r\n> back in section 4.6.2. So it would great if this could somehow be\r\n> improved so that it is not possible for someone to make either of the\r\n> 2\r\n> mistakes because of seeing such an example, thanks.\r\n",
      "createdAt": "2023-10-20T09:40:02Z",
      "updatedAt": "2023-10-20T11:05:05Z",
      "closedAt": "2023-10-20T11:05:05Z",
      "comments": []
    },
