    {
      "number": 21,
      "id": "I_kwDOJTh_ks52eAMD",
      "title": "Appendix for list of changes",
      "url": "https://github.com/boucadair/rfc8407bis/issues/21",
      "state": "CLOSED",
      "author": "boucadair",
      "authorAssociation": "OWNER",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "      The document SHOULD contain an appendix detailing the changes\r\n       from the RFC it is replacing.\r\n\r\nsee https://github.com/tsaad-dev/te/issues/220\r\n\r\nThis is not specific to YANG, but need to check if there is an authoritative ref ",
      "createdAt": "2023-11-10T12:54:30Z",
      "updatedAt": "2023-11-16T08:35:54Z",
      "closedAt": "2023-11-16T08:35:53Z",
      "comments": [
        {
          "author": "boucadair",
          "authorAssociation": "OWNER",
          "body": "No Changes is needed to the bis as this is already covered by:\r\n\r\n> YANG modules under review are likely to be contained in Internet- Drafts (I-Ds). All guidelines for I-D authors [[ID-Guidelines](https://boucadair.github.io/rfc8407bis/draft-ietf-netmod-rfc8407bis.html#ID-Guidelines)] MUST be followed.\r\n\r\nThe ID-Guidelines points to https://authors.ietf.org/required-content, which then have the following:\r\n\r\n```\r\nSummary of Changes\r\nAs noted in the [Abstract](https://authors.ietf.org/en/required-content#abstract) and [Introduction](https://authors.ietf.org/en/required-content#introduction) sections above, the Abstract and Introduction must call out any RFCs an I-D intends to obsolete or update. There should also be a section providing greater detail about the motivation and changes.\r\n\r\nChecklist:\r\n\r\n Ensure the I-D clearly summarizes any changes made from the RFCs being updated or obsoleted.\r\n Ensure any errata against RFCs that are being obsoleted or updated have been considered, and that the I-D clearly identifies those that have been addressed.\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n",
          "createdAt": "2023-11-16T08:35:53Z",
          "updatedAt": "2023-11-16T08:35:53Z"
        }
      ]
    },
